* [**Added**] A separate patch to restore 40MB of memory for Homebrew. Disabled by default. Some games that require EULA acceptance before starting use the browser, which now lacks enough memory and therefore crashes (e.g., Ni No Kuni, Bioshock 3, MGS3, and others).  
  So, if you use mods that lacked memory on FW 21+, enable this patch. If you have games that crash because of it — disable it. As always, the toggle is located in *Uberhand > packages > Settings > 40mb memory on FW20+ status*.  
* [**Added**] A rollback option for users who accidentally enabled the mode intended for consoles with 8GB of RAM.  
  *hekate > payloads > TegraExplorer > Remove_8GB-RAM_config.te*
